# CSS Basics - Design

# Project Overview
This project demonstrates fundamental CSS concepts with an enhanced and creative user interface design.  
It includes background styling, font customization, borders, margin, padding, layout design, and button styling.

The design uses a purple-themed animated gradient background with a glass-style card layout.

# Objectives Covered

- Background color (Animated Gradient)
- Font styling (Typography and spacing)
- Borders (Card and feature boxes)
- Margin (External spacing)
- Padding (Internal spacing)
- Button styling (Hover and transition effects)
- Flexbox layout
- CSS animations

# Files Included

- `index.html` – Main HTML structure
- `style.css` – CSS styling file
- `README.md` – Project documentation

# Design Features

- Animated purple gradient background
- Glassmorphism card design
- Feature boxes with hover effects
- Interactive styled button
- Proper spacing using margin and padding
- Clean and modern layout

# Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox, Animations, Transitions)

# How to Run the Project

1. Download all files.
2. Keep `index.html` and `style.css` in the same folder.
3. Open `index.html` in any web browser.

